SUMMARY:A Fire Upon the Deep - Vernor Vinge
DESCRIPTION:The Sci Fi Book Club\nHi everyone\,\n\nWidely regarded among s
 cience fiction readers and critics as one of the standout space opera nove
 ls of its era\, *A Fire Upon the Deep* has been on my radar for a while bu
 t hasn't made it to our survey. I was glad to see it immediately selected 
 by membership. It's especially touted in hard sci-fi circles\, so it will 
 be a good follow-up after a more fantasy-leaning novel in *Black Sun*.\n\n
 Book of the Month\n*A Fire Upon the Deep -* Vernor Vinge (1992)\n\nMuch of
  *A Fire Upon the Deep*'s reputation comes from its innovative worldbuildi
 ng and unique alien culture. Vinge is generally praised for his writing ch
 ops and being able to balance the concept and the details. As reported in 
 this interesting [Wired article](https://www.wired.com/2022/11/geeks-guide
 -fire-upon-the-deep/)\, the novel "...juggles dozens of characters and plo
 tlines without ever becoming confusing. Science fiction author Abby Goldsm
 ith [says] '...plotwise it’s stunning...the work shows. The amount of ti
 me and effort he put into thinking it through\, I really admire that.'" Al
 l this said\, I've heard that it can be a slow start for some readers and 
 a hill to climb at the beginning. But once it gets going\, it's hard to pu
 t down. Looking forward to hearing your thoughts on this one!\n\nTo join a
  Book Club meeting\, all you will need is YOURSELF. If you haven’t had a
  chance to finish the book\, we still would love for you to join us in the
  discussion.\n\nNot able to join us in person for events? [The Sci Fi Book
  Club is on Discord](https://discord.gg/B9NMnC2F). Join us and keep the co
 nversation going.
